 gem of a one-liner\r\n```rust\r\nlet max_val = (next_hp as f32).max(next_pwr as f32).max(next_def as f32) as i32;\r\n```\r\nThat could just as easily just have been\r\n```rust\r\nlet max_val = next_hp.max(next_pwr).max(next_def);\r\n```\r\nIf i32 implemented `max`.\r\nIt strikes me as odd that a function that seems to be this trivial and useful doesn't exist on integers, but does on floats.\r\n\r\nThere isn't much more to say about the issue, other than that.\r\nIt would certainly be a quality of life improvement if it were to be implemented.", "closed_by": {"login": "ishitatsuyuki", "id": 12389383, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyMzg5Mzgz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12389383?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki", "html_url": "https://github.com/ishitatsuyuki", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ishitatsuyuki/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/60556/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/60556/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}